2) Adding more classes in a package
CODE:
package maths_4;
import package_maths.add;
import package_maths.sub;
public class maths_4 {
 
 public static void main(String[] args) {
 
 add code1=new add();
 code1.display1();
 
 sub code2=new sub();
 code2.display2();
 }
 
}
//Package 1
package package_maths;
public class add {
 int a=5,b=6;
 int c=a+b;
public void display1()
 {
 System.out.println("The result after addition is " +c);
 }
}
//Package 2
package package_maths;
public class sub {
 int a=20,b=10;
 int c=a-b;
public void display2()
 {
 System.out.println("The result after substraction is " +c);
 }
}
OUTPUT:
run:
The result after addition is 11
The result after substraction is 10
BUILD SUCCESSFUL (total time: 0 seconds)
